    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix PUCCH format 3 generation for shortened formats and extended CP\n\n### Summary\nThe `generate_pucch3x()` function in the LTE UE transport layer had multiple issues that caused incorrect PUCCH format 3 signal generation. These issues manifested as garbled uplink signals and failed PUCCH transmission when using shortened formats or extended cyclic prefix configurations.\n\nThe main problems were:\n1. Incorrect payload bit indexing during channel coding\n2. Hardcoded symbol counts that didn't account for CP type or shortened formats\n3. Faulty W sequence selection logic for DMRS and data symbols\n4. Improper symbol offset calculations for extended CP\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure a UE with PUCCH format 3 transmission\n2. Set up a scenario with extended cyclic prefix or shortened PUCCH format\n3. Attempt PUCCH format 3 transmission\n4. Observe incorrect signal generation and potential buffer overruns\n\nThe symptoms include:\n- Incorrect PUCCH signal constellation in uplink traces\n- UE failing to receive ACK/NACK responses from eNB\n- Potential memory access violations in extreme cases\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_UE_TRANSPORT/pucch_ue.c`: \n  - Fixed payload bit indexing in channel coding (line 654)\n  - Corrected symbol offset calculations for extended CP (line 769)\n  - Rewrote W sequence selection logic for robust DMRS/data symbol handling\n  - Updated DFT processing loop to use dynamic symbol counts\n  - Added proper array initialization to prevent undefined behavior\n"
}